 Head to **Mariamman Temple** in Mayanoor – vibrant local worship. Free.\n- **Lunch**\n  - Street\u2011food lunch: biryani or pongal from a reputable stall.  \n    - Approx.\u202f\u20b9120\u202f–\u202f\u20b9180.\n- **Afternoon**\n  - Quick stop at **Kalyana Pasupatheeswarar Temple** for any missed rituals.\n  - Return to hotel, check\u2011out, store luggage at station if needed.\n- **Evening**\n  - Take auto\u2011rickshaw back to Karur Junction.\n  - Board train back to your origin city.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended Hotels (one per category)\n\n| Category | Hotel (near Mayanoor) | Approx. Nightly Rate* |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Budget** | **Hotel Sri Krishna** – basic rooms, clean, 24\u202fh front desk | \u20b91,500\u202f–\u202f\u20b92,000 |\n| **Mid\u2011range** | **Hotel Sree Krishna** – air\u2011conditioned, complimentary breakfast, Wi\u2011Fi | \u20b93,200\u202f–\u202f\u20b94,000 |\n| **Luxury** | **The Karur Residency** – spacious suites, pool, restaurant, valet | \u20b96,500\u202f–\u202f\u20b98,000 |\n\n\\*Rates are per night, inclusive of taxes; actual price may vary by season.\n\n---\n\n## Approximate Budget Summary (per person)\n\n| Item | Budget (\u20b9) | Mid\u2011range (\u20b9) | Luxury (\u20b9) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Train (round\u2011trip) | 1,500 | 1,500 | 1,500 |\n| Local transport (auto, rickshaw, boat) | 500 | 500 | 500 |\n| Meals (2\u202fdays) | 1,200 | 1,800 | 2,400 |\n| Hotel (2\u202fnights) | 3,000 | 7,200 | 14,000 |\n| Entry/guide fees & misc. | 300 | 300 | 300 |\n| **Total Approx.** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b96,500** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b911,300** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b919,200** |\n\nEven the luxury option stays well under the INR\u202f50,000 ceiling, leaving ample room for extra shopping or unexpected expenses.\n\n---\n\n**Tips to stay within budget**\n- Book train tickets and hotel rooms 2\u20113\u202fweeks in advance for best rates.  \n- Use shared auto\u2011rickshaws where possible.  \n- Opt for local eateries; they offer authentic food at low cost.  \n- Carry a small amount of cash for temple donations and market bargaining.\n\nEnjoy your short but enriching getaway to Mayanoor, Karur!  \n\n**APPROVE**', type='TextMessage')}
2026-02-21 15:50:01 - INFO - 410 -{"payload": "{\"message\":{\"id\":\"32fc5a93-9e35-428c-97b7-5c4e6bcecbe6\",\"source\":\"Travel_Planner\",\"models_usage\":{\"prompt_tokens\":208,\"completion_tokens\":1302},\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-02-21T10:20:01.272236Z\",\"content\":\"**Two\u2011Day Mayanoor (Karur) Itinerary \u2013 INR\u202f50,000 budget**\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Day\u202f1 \u2013 Arrival & Exploration\\n- **Morning**\\n  - Depart from your home city by train to **Karur Junction** (e.g., Chennai\u202f\u2192\u202fKarur, ~3\u202fh).  \\n    - Approx.\u202f\u20b91,200\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b91,800 (2nd\u202fclass AC) round\u2011trip.\\n  - Take an auto\u2011rickshaw (\u2248\u202f\u20b9150) to Mayanoor and check\u2011in.\\n- **Mid\u2011Morning**\\n  - Breakfast at a local eatery \u2013 idli, dosa, filter coffee.  \\n    - Approx.\u202f\u20b980\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9120 per person.\\n- **Late Morning**\\n  - Visit **Kalyana Pasupatheeswarar Temple** (ancient Shiva temple, free entry).  \\n    - Optional guide: \u20b9200\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9300.\\n- **Lunch**\\n  - Enjoy a thali at **Sri Krishna Mess** (vegetarian South Indian set).  \\n    - Approx.\u202f\u20b9150\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9200.\\n- **Afternoon**\\n  - Stroll along the **Kaveri River banks**; rent a pedal\u2011boat for a short ride (\u20b9100\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9150).  \\n  - Explore **Karur Handloom & Silk Weaving Centre** \u2013 watch artisans at work (free, small purchase optional).\\n- **Evening**\\n  - Return to hotel, freshen up.\\n  - Dinner at **Hotel Sree Krishna** (non\u2011veg & veg options).  \\n    - Approx.\u202f\u20b9250\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9350 per person.\\n- **Night**\\n  - Optional: Light walk through the town market for souvenirs.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Day\u202f2 \u2013 Culture & Departure\\n- **Morning**\\n  - Early breakfast at hotel (included in stay).\\n  - Visit **Karur Museum** (history, archaeology). Entry: \u20b930\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b950.\\n- **Mid\u2011Morning**\\n  - Head to **Mariamman Temple** in Mayanoor \u2013 vibrant local worship. Free.\\n- **Lunch**\\n  - Street\u2011food lunch: biryani or pongal from a reputable stall.  \\n    - Approx.\u202f\u20b9120\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b9180.\\n- **Afternoon**\\n  - Quick stop at **Kalyana Pasupatheeswarar Temple** for any missed rituals.\\n  - Return to hotel, check\u2011out, store luggage at station if needed.\\n- **Evening**\\n  - Take auto\u2011rickshaw back to Karur Junction.\\n  - Board train back to your origin city.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Recommended Hotels (one per category)\\n\\n| Category | Hotel (near Mayanoor) | Approx. Nightly Rate* |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| **Budget** | **Hotel Sri Krishna** \u2013 basic rooms, clean, 24\u202fh front desk | \u20b91,500\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b92,000 |\\n| **Mid\u2011range** | **Hotel Sree Krishna** \u2013 air\u2011conditioned, complimentary breakfast, Wi\u2011Fi | \u20b93,200\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b94,000 |\\n| **Luxury** | **The Karur Residency** \u2013 spacious suites, pool, restaurant, valet | \u20b96,500\u202f\u2013\u202f\u20b98,000 |\\n\\n\\\\*Rates are per night, inclusive of taxes; actual price may vary by season.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Approximate Budget Summary (per person)\\n\\n| Item | Budget (\u20b9) | Mid\u2011range (\u20b9) | Luxury (\u20b9) |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| Train (round\u2011trip) | 1,500 | 1,500 | 1,500 |\\n| Local transport (auto, rickshaw, boat) | 500 | 500 | 500 |\\n| Meals (2\u202fdays) | 1,200 | 1,800 | 2,400 |\\n| Hotel (2\u202fnights) | 3,000 | 7,200 | 14,000 |\\n| Entry/guide fees & misc. | 300 | 300 | 300 |\\n| **Total Approx.** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b96,500** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b911,300** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b919,200** |\\n\\nEven the luxury option stays well under the INR\u202f50,000 ceiling, leaving ample room for extra shopping or unexpected expenses.\\n\\n---\\n\\n**Tips to stay within budget**\\n- Book train tickets and hotel rooms 2\u20113\u202fweeks in advance for best rates.  \\n- Use shared auto\u2011rickshaws where possible.  \\n- Opt for local eateries; they offer authentic food at low cost.  \\n- Carry a small amount of cash for temple donations and market bargaining.\\n\\nEnjoy your short but enriching getaway to Mayanoor, Karur!  \\n\\n**APPROVE**\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"}}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_60271acf-0df4-4d69-966e-f4ec44f69efc/60271acf-0df4-4d69-966e-f4ec44f69efc", "receiver": "output_topic_60271acf-0df4-4d69-966e-f4ec44f69efc/60271acf-0df4-4d69-966e-f4ec44f69efc", "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.SEND", "type": "Message"}
